Azure offers different support plans to help users resolve issues and optimize their cloud usage.

Plans include:

* Basic (free)
* Developer
* Standard
* Professional Direct

Each plan provides varying levels of support such as response time and technical assistance.

For example, a startup may use basic support, while an enterprise may opt for premium support for faster issue resolution.

A real-life use case is critical systems requiring immediate support during outages.

Another example is developers needing guidance while building applications.

Support plans ensure smooth operation and quick resolution of issues.
